ous, meticulous records; an army of anthropologists could not have achieved a fraction of what he achieved in his short life. Wickwire’s beautifully crafted narrative accords Teit the status he deserves, consolidating his place as a leading and innovative anthropologist in his own right.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnthropologistszBritish ColumbiavBiography. 0aEthnologistszBritish ColumbiavBiography. 0aIndigenous peopleszBritish ColumbiaxSocial life and customsy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311141772140uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486153340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774861533423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774861533/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-141772-1  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles